<paragraph blockId="2.[136,959,1164,1191]" box="[136,959,1164,1191]" pageId="2" pageNumber="79">
<heading box="[136,959,1164,1191]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="2" pageNumber="79" reason="3">
<taxonomicName authority="Kim, Khim, Witkowski and Park" authorityName="Kim, Khim, Witkowski and Park" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,725,1164,1191]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Fogedia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="79" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="orientalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,347,1164,1191]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="79">Fogedia orientalis</emphasis>
Kim, Khim, Witkowski and Park
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[736,823,1165,1191]" pageId="2" pageNumber="79" rank="species">
<emphasis box="[736,761,1165,1190]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="79">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[775,815,1165,1190]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="79">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[838,952,1164,1191]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 2–9" captionStart-1="FIGURES 10–15" captionStartId-0="2.[136,243,1771,1793]" captionStartId-1="3.[136,243,897,919]" captionTargetBox-0="[340,1247,1467,1746]" captionTargetBox-1="[157,1430,245,872]" captionTargetId-0="figure-324@2.[340,1247,1467,1747]" captionTargetId-1="figure-43@3.[157,1430,245,872]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURES 2–9. Fogedia orientalis Kim, Khim, Witkowski and Park, sp. nov. Valves of Fogedia orientalis from Northeast Asia tidal flat. Fig. 2. Specimen from the Korea (KO-BO). Fig. 3. Specimen from the China (CH-YK2). Figs 4, 7-9. Specimens from the Korea (KO-GY). Fig. 5. Specimen from the China (CH-DF). Fig. 6. Specimen from the Korea (KO-GY) as holotype. Scale bar: 10 µm." captionText-1="FIGURES 10–15. SEM photos of Fogedia orientalis Northeast Asia tidal flat; Fig. 10. External view of whole valve; Fig. 11. Central area in external valve view; Fig. 12. Apical area in external valve view; Fig. 13. Overall view of valve interior; Fig. 14. Central area in internal valve view; Fig. 15. Apical area in internal valve view. Scale bars: 1 µm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809831" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809833" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6809831/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6809833/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="79">Figs 2–15</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1236,1443]" pageId="2" pageNumber="79">
LM observations (
<figureCitation box="[351,460,1236,1262]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–9" captionStartId="2.[136,243,1771,1793]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,1467,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-324@2.[340,1247,1467,1747]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2–9. Fogedia orientalis Kim, Khim, Witkowski and Park, sp. nov. Valves of Fogedia orientalis from Northeast Asia tidal flat. Fig. 2. Specimen from the Korea (KO-BO). Fig. 3. Specimen from the China (CH-YK2). Figs 4, 7-9. Specimens from the Korea (KO-GY). Fig. 5. Specimen from the China (CH-DF). Fig. 6. Specimen from the Korea (KO-GY) as holotype. Scale bar: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809831" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809831/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="79">Figs 2–9</figureCitation>
): Valves are elliptic-lanceolate to lanceolate, with acutely-rounded protracted apices, 11.5–21 μm in length and 5.5–6.5 μm in width. External central raphe endings are punctiform, while external apical raphe endings are slightly bent to the same direction. Axial area is very narrow and linear throughout. Central area is small and square in shape, formed by two shortened striae one on each side. Typical lateral area is absent in the valve. Transapical striae parallel in the middle of the valve then becoming slightly radiate towards apices, 
<quantity box="[1264,1364,1380,1407]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.191" metricValueMax="4.572" metricValueMin="3.81" pageId="2" pageNumber="79" unit="in" value="16.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="15.0">15–18 in</quantity>
10 μm. Voigt discordance is barely discernible with LM.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809831" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6809831" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809831/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="79" startId="2.[136,243,1771,1793]" targetBox="[340,1247,1467,1746]" targetPageId="2">
