<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="80" pageId="2" pageNumber="79" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1948,2082]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1451,158,220]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="80" pageId="2" pageNumber="79">
SEM observations (
<figureCitation box="[414,546,1948,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15" captionStartId="3.[136,243,897,919]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,245,872]" captionTargetId="figure-43@3.[157,1430,245,872]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. SEM photos of Fogedia orientalis Northeast Asia tidal flat; Fig. 10. External view of whole valve; Fig. 11. Central area in external valve view; Fig. 12. Apical area in external valve view; Fig. 13. Overall view of valve interior; Fig. 14. Central area in internal valve view; Fig. 15. Apical area in internal valve view. Scale bars: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809833" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809833/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="79">Figs 10–15</figureCitation>
): External valve face is flat with an abrupt transition to the valve mantle. Axial area is straight and symmetrical with very narrow raphe-sternum (
<figureCitation box="[875,958,1984,2010]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15" captionStartId="3.[136,243,897,919]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,245,872]" captionTargetId="figure-43@3.[157,1430,245,872]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. SEM photos of Fogedia orientalis Northeast Asia tidal flat; Fig. 10. External view of whole valve; Fig. 11. Central area in external valve view; Fig. 12. Apical area in external valve view; Fig. 13. Overall view of valve interior; Fig. 14. Central area in internal valve view; Fig. 15. Apical area in internal valve view. Scale bars: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809833" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809833/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="79">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). External central raphe endings are slightly expanded (
<figureCitation box="[261,394,2020,2046]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15" captionStartId="3.[136,243,897,919]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,245,872]" captionTargetId="figure-43@3.[157,1430,245,872]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. SEM photos of Fogedia orientalis Northeast Asia tidal flat; Fig. 10. External view of whole valve; Fig. 11. Central area in external valve view; Fig. 12. Apical area in external valve view; Fig. 13. Overall view of valve interior; Fig. 14. Central area in internal valve view; Fig. 15. Apical area in internal valve view. Scale bars: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809833" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809833/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="79">Figs 10–11</figureCitation>
). The areolae and transapical striae are evenly spaced. Certain areolae near the central area exhibit different shape compared to other areolae, often being circular in shape. The raphe slit runs relatively straight from the central area to the helictoglossa which is relatively simple and small without twist (
<figureCitation box="[1173,1303,158,185]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15" captionStartId="3.[136,243,897,919]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,245,872]" captionTargetId="figure-43@3.[157,1430,245,872]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. SEM photos of Fogedia orientalis Northeast Asia tidal flat; Fig. 10. External view of whole valve; Fig. 11. Central area in external valve view; Fig. 12. Apical area in external valve view; Fig. 13. Overall view of valve interior; Fig. 14. Central area in internal valve view; Fig. 15. Apical area in internal valve view. Scale bars: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809833" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809833/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="80">Figs 13, 15</figureCitation>
). Areolae are internally occluded by thin hymenes.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6809833" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6809833" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6809833/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="80" startId="3.[136,243,897,919]" targetBox="[157,1430,245,872]" targetPageId="3">
